The paper deals with the problem of labeling point features on interactive maps, which is a common task in computer graphics and visualization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GR (Computer Graphics), which deals with the creation, manipulation, and rendering of images and graphical content. 

The paper also employs geometric algorithms and cost analysis to solve the labeling problem, which suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). 

Additionally, the paper deals with the challenge of handling large datasets and providing real-time labeling, which could fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
